
Thomas &quot;Tommy&quot; Rigg (born Bedlington, 20 February 1920, died Northumberland, May 1995)1 was an English professional association footballer, who played as a goalkeeper. His clubs included Watford2 and Gillingham, where he made nearly 200 Football League appearances.3 He was related to Jimmy Kelly, who also played for Watford.4
